  "notes": [
    {
      "id": "72bc6f45-6887-ef11-8474-000d3a37e3b6",
      "type": "GeneralTitle",
      "area": "General",
      "position": 0,
      "content": "IMPORTANT MAJOR INFORMATION",
      "contentHtml": null
    },
    {
      "id": "78bc6f45-6887-ef11-8474-000d3a37e3b6",
      "type": "GeneralText",
      "area": "General",
      "position": 1,
      "content": "The Anthropology B.A. major is designed for students interested in an anthropological understanding of human behavior. One of the strengths of anthropology is its cross-cultural “holistic” and integrative approach with many fields, such as biology, history, linguistics, the social sciences, and many of the humanities. Listed below are the lower division preparation courses for the major. To be considered for this major, please complete two or more courses listed below by the end of spring before transfer: One course in Human Evolution, One course in Archaeology, One course in Sociocultural Anthropology, and One course in Culture and Communication. All courses must be taken for a letter grade. For more information regarding this major and UCLA's transfer selection process, visit https:// anthro.ucla.edu and https:// admission.ucla.edu. PLEASE NOTE: the community college courses listed below have been approved to satisfy the preparation for this major at UCLA, but they may not be exact equivalents of the UCLA courses.",
      "contentHtml": "<p>The Anthropology B.A. major is designed for students interested in an anthropological understanding of human behavior. One of the strengths of anthropology is its cross-cultural “holistic” and integrative approach with many fields, such as biology, history, linguistics, the social sciences, and many of the humanities.</p><p><br></p><p>Listed below are the lower division preparation courses for the major.</p><p><br></p><p>To be considered for this major, <strong><u>please complete two or more courses listed below</u></strong> by the end of spring before transfer:</p><ul><li>One course in Human Evolution,</li><li>One course in Archaeology,</li><li>One course in Sociocultural Anthropology, and</li><li>One course in Culture and Communication.</li></ul><p>All courses must be taken for a letter grade.</p><p><br></p><p>For more information regarding this major and UCLA's transfer selection process, visit <u style=\"color: rgb(41, 98, 255);\">https://</u><a href=\"http://www.anthro.ucla.edu\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">anthro.ucla.edu</a> and <u style=\"color: rgb(41, 98, 255);\">https://</u><a href=\"http://www.admission.ucla.edu.E\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">admission.ucla.edu.</a></p><p><br></p><p>PLEASE NOTE: the community college courses listed below have been approved to satisfy the preparation for this major at UCLA, but they may not be exact equivalents of the UCLA courses.</p>"
    }
